ss initialization occurs at runtime in a native image context and what the reachability metadata might entail. I need to dig into that metadata.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_TQsPIzPqBLgEQWnM03Z8lsBk|fc_0bce82438a9b6c150169f738bbcf8c8196bea9bc2a433dc3db\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"metadata/cglib/cglib/3.3.0/reachability-metadata.json\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1644, \"output\": 893, \"cacheRead\": 31232, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 33769, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777809578974, \"responseId\": \"resp_0bce82438a9b6c150169f738ab71f4819689abb253b4ccc1ae\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_TQsPIzPqBLgEQWnM03Z8lsBk|fc_0bce82438a9b6c150169f738bbcf8c8196bea9bc2a433dc3db\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"{}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777809597098}]}\nhuman-intervention-logs/cglib:cglib:3.3.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-03T12-02-13-400819Z.log:2610:[tool-call] delta {\"path\":\"tests/src/cglib/cglib/3.3.0/src/test/java/cglib/cglib/NetSfCglibCoreReflectUtilsTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage cglib.cglib;\\n\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Constructor;\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\\nimport java.util.Base64;\\nimport java.util.List;\\n\\nimport net.sf.cglib.core.ReflectUtils;\\n\\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class NetSfCglibCoreReflectUtilsTest {\\n    pri